8b44a039a049e24f9224575%2Fgettyimages-2228117604.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+430/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2F74%2F7ac478b44a039a049e24f9224575%2Fgettyimages-2228117604.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+430/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2F74%2F7ac478b44a039a049e24f9224575%2Fgettyimages-2228117604.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+430/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2F74%2F7ac478b44a039a049e24f9224575%2Fgettyimages-2228117604.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+430/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2F74%2F7ac478b44a039a049e24f9224575%2Fgettyimages-2228117604.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+430/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2F74%2F7ac478b44a039a049e24f9224575%2Fgettyimages-2228117604.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+430/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2F74%2F7ac478b44a039a049e24f9224575%2Fgettyimages-2228117604.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+430/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2F74%2F7ac478b44a039a049e24f9224575%2Fgettyimages-2228117604.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+430/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2F74%2F7ac478b44a039a049e24f9224575%2Fgettyimages-2228117604.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+430/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2F74%2F7ac478b44a039a049e24f9224575%2Fgettyimages-2228117604.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8256x4644+0+430/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fe4%2F74%2F7ac478b44a039a049e24f9224575%2Fgettyimages-2228117604.jpg" class="img" alt="A view of the newly paved Rose Garden is seen at the White House in Washington, DC, on August 6, 2025. US President Donald Trump converted the grass portion of the Rose Garden into a patio space, inspired by his Mar-a-Lago club in Florida." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 A view of the newly paved Rose Garden is seen at the White House in Washington, DC, on August 6, 2025. US President Donald Trump converted the grass portion of the Rose Garden into a patio space, inspired by his Mar-a-Lago club in Florida.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Brendan Smialowski/AFP via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The White House is giving the iconic Rose Garden a makeover, and the work is nearly complete. Since returning to office in January, Trump has been on a mission to renovate. He swapped out the grass in the garden with stone, turning what had been a lawn into a patio. The switch bears a striking resemblance to a popular feature at the president's Mar-a-Lago resort in Palm Beach, Fla. The president said it was important to get rid of the grass because it got too soggy for fine footwear. Though the lawn is gone, the flowers will remain a fixture. The Rose Garden dates back to the Kennedy administration. Check out this &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/23/nx-s1-5509554/rose-garden-paved" target="_blank"&gt;look at the popular garden through the years&lt;/a&gt;, including the new renovations.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-84445" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 4000;         --source-height: 2250;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+375/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faa%2F48%2F1a42de894c57bd0e19094b1483db%2F20250731-140739.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+375/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faa%2F48%2F1a42de894c57bd0e19094b1483db%2F20250731-140739.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+375/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faa%2F48%2F1a42de894c57bd0e19094b1483db%2F20250731-140739.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+375/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faa%2F48%2F1a42de894c57bd0e19094b1483db%2F20250731-140739.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+375/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faa%2F48%2F1a42de894c57bd0e19094b1483db%2F20250731-140739.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+375/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faa%2F48%2F1a42de894c57bd0e19094b1483db%2F20250731-140739.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+375/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faa%2F48%2F1a42de894c57bd0e19094b1483db%2F20250731-140739.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+375/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faa%2F48%2F1a42de894c57bd0e19094b1483db%2F20250731-140739.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+375/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faa%2F48%2F1a42de894c57bd0e19094b1483db%2F20250731-140739.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+375/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faa%2F48%2F1a42de894c57bd0e19094b1483db%2F20250731-140739.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+375/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faa%2F48%2F1a42de894c57bd0e19094b1483db%2F20250731-140739.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+375/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faa%2F48%2F1a42de894c57bd0e19094b1483db%2F20250731-140739.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+375/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faa%2F48%2F1a42de894c57bd0e19094b1483db%2F20250731-140739.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+375/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faa%2F48%2F1a42de894c57bd0e19094b1483db%2F20250731-140739.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+375/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faa%2F48%2F1a42de894c57bd0e19094b1483db%2F20250731-140739.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+375/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faa%2F48%2F1a42de894c57bd0e19094b1483db%2F20250731-140739.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+375/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faa%2F48%2F1a42de894c57bd0e19094b1483db%2F20250731-140739.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+375/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Faa%2F48%2F1a42de894c57bd0e19094b1483db%2F20250731-140739.jpg" class="img" alt="The state of Michigan&amp;#039;s tourism campaign created the FRESH scent to promote the state. It&amp;#039;s sold as a blend of beach days, wineries," loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 The state of Michigan's tourism campaign created the FRESH scent to promote the state. It's sold as a blend of Michigan's beach days, wineries, lavender fields and laughter.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Colin Jackson/NPR                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;The state of Michigan's tourism campaign, Pure Michigan, has &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/24/nx-s1-5506282/michigan-fragrance-beach-scents" target="_blank"&gt;created a room and body spray&lt;/a&gt; for the summer. The fragrances are intended to promote the state as a destination for mindful travel.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Ashley Ludlow's mother died in the hospital in 2005. Following her mother's wishes, Ludlow made the difficult decision not to have her resuscitated, a choice that weighed heavily on her. A few days after her mother's death, a nurse reached out to her. The unsung hero &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/25/nx-s1-5511240/unsung-hero-nurse-dnr-death" target="_blank"&gt;offered words of reassurance&lt;/a&gt; about the decision Ludlow had made.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;SpaceX postponed its 10th test launch of its massive Starship rocket yesterday due to a technical glitch. But don't worry, space enthusiasts. If they can overcome the issue, there is a chance they will &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/24/nx-s1-5514847/spacex-starship-rocket-launch" target="_blank"&gt;try again today or tomorrow&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
