ource srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3600x2025+0+375/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2Fac%2Fee92cca94338bb012334037b9470%2Fbuscabulla-0210-pc-quique-cabanillas-300dpi.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3600x2025+0+375/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2Fac%2Fee92cca94338bb012334037b9470%2Fbuscabulla-0210-pc-quique-cabanillas-300dpi.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3600x2025+0+375/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2Fac%2Fee92cca94338bb012334037b9470%2Fbuscabulla-0210-pc-quique-cabanillas-300dpi.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3600x2025+0+375/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2Fac%2Fee92cca94338bb012334037b9470%2Fbuscabulla-0210-pc-quique-cabanillas-300dpi.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3600x2025+0+375/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2Fac%2Fee92cca94338bb012334037b9470%2Fbuscabulla-0210-pc-quique-cabanillas-300dpi.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3600x2025+0+375/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2Fac%2Fee92cca94338bb012334037b9470%2Fbuscabulla-0210-pc-quique-cabanillas-300dpi.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3600x2025+0+375/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2Fac%2Fee92cca94338bb012334037b9470%2Fbuscabulla-0210-pc-quique-cabanillas-300dpi.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3600x2025+0+375/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2Fac%2Fee92cca94338bb012334037b9470%2Fbuscabulla-0210-pc-quique-cabanillas-300dpi.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3600x2025+0+375/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2Fac%2Fee92cca94338bb012334037b9470%2Fbuscabulla-0210-pc-quique-cabanillas-300dpi.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3600x2025+0+375/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2Fac%2Fee92cca94338bb012334037b9470%2Fbuscabulla-0210-pc-quique-cabanillas-300dpi.jpg" class="img" alt="Buscabulla" loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Buscabulla                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Quique Cabanillas/Courtesy of the artist                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Check out what &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/culture/" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NPR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt; is watching, reading and listening to this weekend:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🍿 Movies:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/21/nx-s1-5503422/lurker-movie-review" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Lurker&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; follows a sociopathic striver who maneuvers his way into the inner circle of a rising pop star. NPR's Aisha Harris says the tension in the parasocial relationship between the two main characters, Matthew and Oliver, is deeply satisfying in its unease. And, here are some of the films &lt;a href="http://npr.org/2025/08/22/nx-s1-5508092/ne-zha-2-lurker-honey-dont-in-theaters-this-weekend" target="_blank"&gt;in theaters this weekend&lt;/a&gt;, including a box office record setter you probably haven't heard of.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📺 TV:&lt;/strong&gt; Amanda Knox made headlines in 2007 when her British roommate was found dead in Italy. She's the executive producer of the new eight-part series dramatizing the tale of her wrongful conviction, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/20/nx-s1-5471356/amanda-knox-hulu-show-monica-lewinsky" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Twisted Tale of Amanda Knox&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📚 Books:&lt;/strong&gt; Louis Sachar has spent nearly half a century writing some of my favorite children's books, including &lt;em&gt;Holes&lt;/em&gt; and the Wayside School series. He hopes the adults who grew up on his books will feel the same connection to his latest release, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/21/nx-s1-5501158/louis-sachar-holes-magician-of-tiger-castle" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Magician of Tiger Castle&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. And, here are some of &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/19/nx-s1-5489719/new-books-james-baldwin-bill-mckibben" target="_blank"&gt;this week's publishing highlights&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🎵 Music:&lt;/strong&gt; Puerto Rican duo Buscabulla joins NPR's &lt;em&gt;World Cafe&lt;/em&gt; to &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=g-s1-83939:g-s1-83956" target="_blank"&gt;perform some of their new music&lt;/a&gt; and discuss the making of their latest album, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/world-cafe/2025/08/20/g-s1-83939/buscabulla-album-se-amaba-asi" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Se Amaba Asi&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, which explores vulnerability and romantic hardships.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-84192" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 6000;         --source-height: 3373;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3373+0+185/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F5e%2Fcc41119e46aabc8df3525b0ece25%2Fgettyimages-2229134380.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3373+0+185/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F5e%2Fcc41119e46aabc8df3525b0ece25%2Fgettyimages-2229134380.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3373+0+185/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F5e%2Fcc41119e46aabc8df3525b0ece25%2Fgettyimages-2229134380.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3373+0+185/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F5e%2Fcc41119e46aabc8df3525b0ece25%2Fgettyimages-2229134380.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3373+0+185/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F5e%2Fcc41119e46aabc8df3525b0ece25%2Fgettyimages-2229134380.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3373+0+185/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F5e%2Fcc41119e46aabc8df3525b0ece25%2Fgettyimages-2229134380.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3373+0+185/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F5e%2Fcc41119e46aabc8df3525b0ece25%2Fgettyimages-2229134380.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3373+0+185/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F5e%2Fcc41119e46aabc8df3525b0ece25%2Fgettyimages-2229134380.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3373+0+185/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F5e%2Fcc41119e46aabc8df3525b0ece25%2Fgettyimages-2229134380.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3373+0+185/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F5e%2Fcc41119e46aabc8df3525b0ece25%2Fgettyimages-2229134380.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3373+0+185/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F5e%2Fcc41119e46aabc8df3525b0ece25%2Fgettyimages-2229134380.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3373+0+185/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F5e%2Fcc41119e46aabc8df3525b0ece25%2Fgettyimages-2229134380.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3373+0+185/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F5e%2Fcc41119e46aabc8df3525b0ece25%2Fgettyimages-2229134380.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3373+0+185/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F5e%2Fcc41119e46aabc8df3525b0ece25%2Fgettyimages-2229134380.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3373+0+185/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F5e%2Fcc41119e46aabc8df3525b0ece25%2Fgettyimages-2229134380.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3373+0+185/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F5e%2Fcc41119e46aabc8df3525b0ece25%2Fgettyimages-2229134380.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3373+0+185/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F5e%2Fcc41119e46aabc8df3525b0ece25%2Fgettyimages-2229134380.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3373+0+185/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F78%2F5e%2Fcc41119e46aabc8df3525b0ece25%2Fgettyimages-2229134380.jpg" class="img" alt="Children cool off in a mist fountain in central Paris amid a heatwave, on Aug. 13." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Children cool off in a mist fountain in central Paris amid a heatwave, on Aug. 13.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Dimitar Dilkoff/AFP via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;As European summers grow hotter, a heated political debate is brewing in France over an unsuspecting appliance: the &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/19/nx-s1-5506223/in-france-debate-heats-up-over-air-conditioning" target="_blank"&gt;air conditioner&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;More than 3.6 million children were born in the U.S. in 2020, during the COVID-19 pandemic. As these "COVID kindergarteners" enter school for the first time, many &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/21/nx-s1-5506258/are-covid-kindergarteners-ready-for-school" target="_blank"&gt;parents are anxious&lt;/a&gt; about how their time in isolation will impact their development.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Far fewer Canadians are traveling to the U.S. this year. The dip comes as &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/21/nx-s1-5508461/fewer-canadians-visiting-us" target="_blank"&gt;relations between the two countries are strained&lt;/a&gt; after Trump imposed steep tariffs on Canada and vowed to make it a U.S. state.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Yvonne Dennis.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
