htspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F65%2Fbc%2F03b40ac541aa835dd54241b94d87%2F20250727-npr-bad-bunny-residencia-49.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+209/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F65%2Fbc%2F03b40ac541aa835dd54241b94d87%2F20250727-npr-bad-bunny-residencia-49.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+209/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F65%2Fbc%2F03b40ac541aa835dd54241b94d87%2F20250727-npr-bad-bunny-residencia-49.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+209/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F65%2Fbc%2F03b40ac541aa835dd54241b94d87%2F20250727-npr-bad-bunny-residencia-49.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+209/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F65%2Fbc%2F03b40ac541aa835dd54241b94d87%2F20250727-npr-bad-bunny-residencia-49.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+209/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F65%2Fbc%2F03b40ac541aa835dd54241b94d87%2F20250727-npr-bad-bunny-residencia-49.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+209/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F65%2Fbc%2F03b40ac541aa835dd54241b94d87%2F20250727-npr-bad-bunny-residencia-49.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+209/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F65%2Fbc%2F03b40ac541aa835dd54241b94d87%2F20250727-npr-bad-bunny-residencia-49.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+209/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F65%2Fbc%2F03b40ac541aa835dd54241b94d87%2F20250727-npr-bad-bunny-residencia-49.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+209/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F65%2Fbc%2F03b40ac541aa835dd54241b94d87%2F20250727-npr-bad-bunny-residencia-49.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2250+0+209/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F65%2Fbc%2F03b40ac541aa835dd54241b94d87%2F20250727-npr-bad-bunny-residencia-49.jpg" class="img" alt="Bad Bunny performs at the Jose Miguel Agrelot Coliseum, known as ‘El Choli’, for his residency concert on Sunday, July 27, 2025, in San Juan, P.R. World renowned Puerto Rican artist Benito A. Martinez Ocasio, known as Bad Bunny, is currently performing a 30-show residency in San Juan, Puerto Rico. Titled &amp;quot;I Don&amp;#039;t Want to Leave Here” (&amp;quot;No Me Quiero Ir De Aquí&amp;quot;, in Spanish) the series of weekend concerts will attract over 500,000 people as it celebrates Puerto Rican culture, mirroring the themes of his recent album, Debí Tirar Más Fotos (&amp;quot;I Should Have Taken More Photos&amp;quot;, in English). (Erika P. Rodríguez for NPR)" loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Bad Bunny performs at the Jose Miguel Agrelot Coliseum, known as 'El Choli', for his residency concert on Sunday, July 27, 2025, in San Juan, P.R.  World renowned Puerto Rican artist Benito A. Martinez Ocasio, known as Bad Bunny, is currently performing a 30-show residency in San Juan, Puerto Rico. Titled "I Don't Want to Leave Here" ("No Me Quiero Ir De Aquí", in Spanish) the series of weekend concerts will attract over 500,000 people as it celebrates Puerto Rican culture, mirroring the themes of his recent album, Debí Tirar Más Fotos ("I Should Have Taken More Photos", in English). (Erika P. Rodríguez for NPR)                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          ‎/Erika P. Rodríguez for NPR                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Bad Bunny's 30-concert residency in San Juan has instilled pride in Puerto Rican culture and helped ease the sorrow many feel about leaving their island. A decades-long debt crisis, worsening infrastructure, rising prices from gentrification, and declining services have compelled many Puerto Ricans to search for new opportunities elsewhere. The Puerto Rican rapper's concerts have brought thousands back to the island. His residency is titled "No Me Quiero Ir De Aquí," which means "I Don't Want To Leave Here," hinting at those wounds. On stage, the artist addresses the pain directly, reminding his fans that it doesn't matter where they live, they are no less Puerto Rican. See how Bad Bunny and his fans are &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/16/g-s1-82965/for-puerto-ricans-on-and-off-the-island-bad-bunnys-concert-feels-like-home" target="_blank"&gt;celebrating the island's culture&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-83305" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 4878;         --source-height: 2744;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4878x2744+0+254/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc0%2Faf%2F47a979914324be715a7dfa0f22f7%2F0729-talia-suskauer-and-max-chernin-in-the-national-tour-of-parade-photo-by-joan-marcus.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4878x2744+0+254/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc0%2Faf%2F47a979914324be715a7dfa0f22f7%2F0729-talia-suskauer-and-max-chernin-in-the-national-tour-of-parade-photo-by-joan-marcus.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4878x2744+0+254/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc0%2Faf%2F47a979914324be715a7dfa0f22f7%2F0729-talia-suskauer-and-max-chernin-in-the-national-tour-of-parade-photo-by-joan-marcus.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4878x2744+0+254/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc0%2Faf%2F47a979914324be715a7dfa0f22f7%2F0729-talia-suskauer-and-max-chernin-in-the-national-tour-of-parade-photo-by-joan-marcus.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4878x2744+0+254/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc0%2Faf%2F47a979914324be715a7dfa0f22f7%2F0729-talia-suskauer-and-max-chernin-in-the-national-tour-of-parade-photo-by-joan-marcus.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4878x2744+0+254/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc0%2Faf%2F47a979914324be715a7dfa0f22f7%2F0729-talia-suskauer-and-max-chernin-in-the-national-tour-of-parade-photo-by-joan-marcus.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4878x2744+0+254/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc0%2Faf%2F47a979914324be715a7dfa0f22f7%2F0729-talia-suskauer-and-max-chernin-in-the-national-tour-of-parade-photo-by-joan-marcus.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4878x2744+0+254/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc0%2Faf%2F47a979914324be715a7dfa0f22f7%2F0729-talia-suskauer-and-max-chernin-in-the-national-tour-of-parade-photo-by-joan-marcus.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4878x2744+0+254/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc0%2Faf%2F47a979914324be715a7dfa0f22f7%2F0729-talia-suskauer-and-max-chernin-in-the-national-tour-of-parade-photo-by-joan-marcus.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4878x2744+0+254/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc0%2Faf%2F47a979914324be715a7dfa0f22f7%2F0729-talia-suskauer-and-max-chernin-in-the-national-tour-of-parade-photo-by-joan-marcus.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4878x2744+0+254/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc0%2Faf%2F47a979914324be715a7dfa0f22f7%2F0729-talia-suskauer-and-max-chernin-in-the-national-tour-of-parade-photo-by-joan-marcus.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4878x2744+0+254/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc0%2Faf%2F47a979914324be715a7dfa0f22f7%2F0729-talia-suskauer-and-max-chernin-in-the-national-tour-of-parade-photo-by-joan-marcus.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4878x2744+0+254/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc0%2Faf%2F47a979914324be715a7dfa0f22f7%2F0729-talia-suskauer-and-max-chernin-in-the-national-tour-of-parade-photo-by-joan-marcus.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4878x2744+0+254/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc0%2Faf%2F47a979914324be715a7dfa0f22f7%2F0729-talia-suskauer-and-max-chernin-in-the-national-tour-of-parade-photo-by-joan-marcus.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4878x2744+0+254/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc0%2Faf%2F47a979914324be715a7dfa0f22f7%2F0729-talia-suskauer-and-max-chernin-in-the-national-tour-of-parade-photo-by-joan-marcus.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4878x2744+0+254/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc0%2Faf%2F47a979914324be715a7dfa0f22f7%2F0729-talia-suskauer-and-max-chernin-in-the-national-tour-of-parade-photo-by-joan-marcus.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4878x2744+0+254/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc0%2Faf%2F47a979914324be715a7dfa0f22f7%2F0729-talia-suskauer-and-max-chernin-in-the-national-tour-of-parade-photo-by-joan-marcus.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4878x2744+0+254/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fc0%2Faf%2F47a979914324be715a7dfa0f22f7%2F0729-talia-suskauer-and-max-chernin-in-the-national-tour-of-parade-photo-by-joan-marcus.jpg" class="img" alt="Lucille and Leo Frank, played by Talia Suskauer and Max Chernin, in the national tour of Parade, about a Jewish man falsely accused of murder in 1913. Parade ends its run at the Kennedy Center in Washington D.C.." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Lucille and Leo Frank, played by Talia Suskauer and Max Chernin, in the national tour of &lt;em&gt;Parade&lt;/em&gt;, about a Jewish man falsely accused of murder in 1913.  &lt;em&gt;Parade&lt;/em&gt; ends its run at the Kennedy Center in Washington D.C..                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Joan Marcus                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Parade&lt;/em&gt;, a Tony Award-winning musical about the real-life lynching of a Jewish man in 1915, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/19/nx-s1-5499383/parade-trump-kennedy-center" target="_blank"&gt;arrives at the Kennedy Center this week&lt;/a&gt; amid antisemitic backlash against the show's subject.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;For two days each August, a tractor pull, a grassroots motorsport like no other, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/15/nx-s1-5492185/grassroots-motorsport-pulls-tractors-and-trucks" target="_blank"&gt;draws big crowds to a hamlet&lt;/a&gt; in Western New York.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Newsmax has agreed to pay $67 million to &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/08/18/nx-s1-5506062/newsmax-pays-67-million-to-settle-defamation-case-linked-to-2020-election-coverage" target="_blank"&gt;settle a defamation lawsuit&lt;/a&gt; against the news organization for broadcasting false claims that the 2020 election was rigged.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
