/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F19%2F0d%2Fdafa5ab84dbf927cc0249c7f821d%2F186071607-mike-sizemore-20150805-084-pyongyang-kp-kim-il-sung-square.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+5/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F19%2F0d%2Fdafa5ab84dbf927cc0249c7f821d%2F186071607-mike-sizemore-20150805-084-pyongyang-kp-kim-il-sung-square.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+5/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F19%2F0d%2Fdafa5ab84dbf927cc0249c7f821d%2F186071607-mike-sizemore-20150805-084-pyongyang-kp-kim-il-sung-square.jpg" class="img" alt="Two kids play in Kim II Sung Square " loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Two kids play in Kim II Sung Square.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Mike Sizemore                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It is no surprise to Mike Sizemore that it is hot in Pyongyang, North Korea, in August. One afternoon, the 44-year-old from Charleston, W.Va., and his guides stood at the end of Kim II Sung Square, hoping for a breeze as they watched hundreds of schoolchildren practice for an Independence Day celebration later that month. The kids took a quick break. Everything was quiet for a moment, then two girls leaped to their feet and started chasing one another around, laughing and shouting. Many years later, Sizemore still sometimes thinks about them and hopes their spirits remain unbroken. "Wherever you go, it's people. It's always about the people," Sizemore said. "Among the photos I've taken, my favorites are of individuals just getting through the day."&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sizemore's tip:&lt;/strong&gt; "Look around. Take all the photos you can. Every photo captures a piece of today, and tomorrow, even a mediocre photo might make someone pause and say, 'Wow!'"&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-83492" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 5058;         --source-height: 2845;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5058x2845+0+527/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2d%2Fab%2F0c5c4a9e4844a3cccd0176b73eae%2F186071607-if-and-when2856.jpeg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5058x2845+0+527/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2d%2Fab%2F0c5c4a9e4844a3cccd0176b73eae%2F186071607-if-and-when2856.jpeg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5058x2845+0+527/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2d%2Fab%2F0c5c4a9e4844a3cccd0176b73eae%2F186071607-if-and-when2856.jpeg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5058x2845+0+527/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2d%2Fab%2F0c5c4a9e4844a3cccd0176b73eae%2F186071607-if-and-when2856.jpeg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5058x2845+0+527/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2d%2Fab%2F0c5c4a9e4844a3cccd0176b73eae%2F186071607-if-and-when2856.jpeg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5058x2845+0+527/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2d%2Fab%2F0c5c4a9e4844a3cccd0176b73eae%2F186071607-if-and-when2856.jpeg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5058x2845+0+527/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2d%2Fab%2F0c5c4a9e4844a3cccd0176b73eae%2F186071607-if-and-when2856.jpeg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5058x2845+0+527/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2d%2Fab%2F0c5c4a9e4844a3cccd0176b73eae%2F186071607-if-and-when2856.jpeg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5058x2845+0+527/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2d%2Fab%2F0c5c4a9e4844a3cccd0176b73eae%2F186071607-if-and-when2856.jpeg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5058x2845+0+527/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2d%2Fab%2F0c5c4a9e4844a3cccd0176b73eae%2F186071607-if-and-when2856.jpeg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5058x2845+0+527/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2d%2Fab%2F0c5c4a9e4844a3cccd0176b73eae%2F186071607-if-and-when2856.jpeg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5058x2845+0+527/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2d%2Fab%2F0c5c4a9e4844a3cccd0176b73eae%2F186071607-if-and-when2856.jpeg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5058x2845+0+527/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2d%2Fab%2F0c5c4a9e4844a3cccd0176b73eae%2F186071607-if-and-when2856.jpeg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5058x2845+0+527/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2d%2Fab%2F0c5c4a9e4844a3cccd0176b73eae%2F186071607-if-and-when2856.jpeg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5058x2845+0+527/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2d%2Fab%2F0c5c4a9e4844a3cccd0176b73eae%2F186071607-if-and-when2856.jpeg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5058x2845+0+527/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2d%2Fab%2F0c5c4a9e4844a3cccd0176b73eae%2F186071607-if-and-when2856.jpeg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5058x2845+0+527/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2d%2Fab%2F0c5c4a9e4844a3cccd0176b73eae%2F186071607-if-and-when2856.jpeg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5058x2845+0+527/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2d%2Fab%2F0c5c4a9e4844a3cccd0176b73eae%2F186071607-if-and-when2856.jpeg" class="img" alt="A band holds a charity concert in Kevin Pickard&amp;#039;s neighborhood." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 A band holds a charity concert in Kevin Pickard's neighborhood.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Kevin Pickard                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;When one of Kevin Pickard's neighbors needed help paying for chemotherapy, they turned to the community. Another neighbor's son announced he would hold a charity concert in his parents' driveway to help. The 45-year-old from West Point, Utah, says the kid's band was so good and full of life. He snapped this picture of the simple but beautiful stage design with the bright setting sun behind the organizer and lead singer. "This kid is not following a traditional path towards what most people would call 'success,' but this selfless act of charity defines a successful life, in my book," Pickard said.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pickard's tip: &lt;/strong&gt;"Keep trying! Have fun, gain experience, be patient with yourself and others."&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Love for home&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-83490" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 3300;         --source-height: 1856;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3300x1856+0+939/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fef%2F89%2F0d6ad1d742b48c6ea813208c3ad8%2F186071607-the-beat-of-the-street-liz-daino-photography.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3300x1856+0+939/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fef%2F89%2F0d6ad1d742b48c6ea813208c3ad8%2F186071607-the-beat-of-the-street-li